{"image_id": "ATO_2017_page_38", "image_size": [1257, 1613], "ocr": [{"text": "included in revenue is influenced by the cost of gas and the level of gas sales volumes. We record the associated", "bbox": [153.2, 140.4, 1090.9, 161.2]}, {"text": "tax expense as a component of taxes, other than income. Although changes in revenue related taxes arising from", "bbox": [153.2, 165.4, 1090.8, 186.2]}, {"text": "changes in gas costs affect gross profit, over time the impact is offset within operating income.", "bbox": [153.2, 190.4, 945.1, 211.3]}, {"text": "Although the cost of gas typically does not have a direct impact on our gross profit, higher gas costs may", "bbox": [194.9, 229.1, 1071.8, 249.9]}, {"text": "adversely impact our accounts receivable collections, resulting in higher bad debt expense, and may require us to", "bbox": [153.2, 254.1, 1097.5, 274.9]}, {"text": "increase borrowings under our credit facilities resulting in higher interest expense. In addition, higher gas costs,", "bbox": [153.2, 279.1, 1086.1, 299.9]}, {"text": "as well as competitive factors in the industry and general economic conditions may cause customers to conserve", "bbox": [153.2, 304.1, 1090.5, 324.9]}, {"text": "or, in the case of industrial consumers, to use alternative energy sources. Currently, gas cost risk has been miti-", "bbox": [153.2, 329.1, 1081.4, 349.9]}, {"text": "gated by rate design that allows us to collect from our customers the gas cost portion of our bad debt expense on", "bbox": [153.2, 354.1, 1091.1, 374.9]}, {"text": "approximately 76 percent of our residential and commercial margins.", "bbox": [153.2, 379.1, 731.5, 400.0]}, {"text": "During fiscal 2017, we completed 18 regulatory proceedings in our distribution segment, which should", "bbox": [194.9, 417.8, 1054.8, 438.6]}, {"text": "result in a $91.2 million increase in annual operating income.", "bbox": [153.2, 442.8, 665.4, 463.6]}, {"text": "Review of Financial and Operating Results", "bbox": [174.1, 495.0,